
I was delighted to receive your charming note. As you know I love your prose; to get it in this personal form enhances the pleasure it gives me.1

I wish you a very happy New Year.

Cordially,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: FREDERIC W. HILLS

TL (XEROX), 1 p.





Montreux-Palace Hotel

1820 Montreux, Switzerland

February 11, 1974

Dear Mr. Hills,

I am a little upset by your cable of February 7 in which you ask me to provide a description of my new novel for your Fall catalogue.

